The paper proposes a deep learning framework for detecting and restoring artifacts in endoscopy videos, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as object detection, image restoration, and quality assessment. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses generative adversarial networks (GANs) for image restoration, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for object detection and classification, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a quality metric for assessing frame quality, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
